Search

Search module provides an architecture for storing and searching page documents in Elasticsearch in a generalized way.

 

Latest version: 8.3.1 View on GitHub
Last update: 15 Oct 2018
 
  Type: Core Splitted
Group: Functional

API (Facades)

Facade Method Description
install

  • Loads index definition json files from the folders

  • Installs Elasticsearch indexes and mapping types based on the loaded index definitions if they not exists already

  • For each configured store a separated index name is generated

  • The index is created for only the current store

  • The name of the index is automatically prefixed with the store name + underscore

  • Generates IndexMap class for each mapping type

  • The generated IndexMaps are not store specific and has the class name of the mapping types suffixed with "IndexMap"

  • The generated files will be removed and re-created always when install runs
getTotalCount

  • Returns the total number of documents in the current index
getMetaData

  • Returns the metadata information from the current index

  • Returns empty array if the index is not installed
delete

  • Removes the current index
getDocument

  • Returns a document from the current index with the given key in the given mapping type
searchKeys

  • Runs a simple full text search for the given search string

  • Returns the raw result set ordered by relevance
transformPageMapToDocument

{@inheritdoc}
transformPageMapToDocumentByMapperName

  • Transforms a raw data array into an Elasticsearch "page" mapping type document

  • The transformation is based on the given page map plugin name what configures which data goes into which field
generatePageIndexMap

  • Loads index definition json files from the folders

  • Generates IndexMap class for each mapping type

  • The generated IndexMaps are not store specific and has the class name of the mapping types suffixed with "IndexMap"

  • The generated files will be removed and re-created always when the command runs
createSnapshot

  • Creates a Snapshot.
existsSnapshot

  • Checks if a Snapshot exists.
deleteSnapshot

  • Deletes a Snapshot.
existsSnapshotRepository

  • Checks if a Snapshot repository exists.
createSnapshotRepository

  • Creates a Snapshot repository.
restoreSnapshot

  • Restores a Snapshot.
closeIndex

  • Closes an Index.
openIndex

  • Opens an Index.
closeAllIndices

  • Closes all indices.
copyIndex

  • Copies one index to another index.

Clients

Client Method Description
checkConnection

  • Connects to Elasticsearch client if possible

  • Throws exception if connection fails
expandQuery

  • Expands the base search query with multiple query expanders

  • All expanders use the same search configuration provided by this client

  • The expanders use the given parameters to adapt to the request

  • Returns the expanded query
search

  • Runs the search query based on the search configuration provided by this client

  • If there's no result formatter given then the raw search result will be returned

  • The formatted search result will be an associative array where the keys are the name and the values are the formatted results
getSearchConfig

  • Returns a statically cached instance (for performance reasons) of the search configuration

  • The result is the union of the hard-coded and the dynamic configurations

  • Dynamic configuration is provided by \Spryker\Client\Search\SearchDependencyProvider::createSearchConfigExpanderPlugins()
searchKeys

  • Runs a simple full text search for the given search string

  • Returns the raw result set ordered by relevance
searchQueryString

  • Runs a string search for the given search string

  • @see https://www.elastic.co/guide/en/elasticsearch/reference/2.4/query-dsl-query-string-query.html

  • Returns the raw result set ordered by relevance
read

  • Returns data from an external search service (e.g Elasticsearch)
write

  • Writes data into an external search service (e.g Elasticsearch)
writeBulk

  • Writes data into an external search service in bulk mode.
delete

  • Deletes data from an external search service (e.g Elasticsearch)
deleteBulk

  • Deletes data from an external search service (e.g Elasticsearch) in bulk mode.

Plugins

Plugin Method Description
/​src/​Spryker/​Zed/​Search/​Dependency/​Plugin/​NamedPageMapInterface.php getName

  • This name will use for mapping specific type to a proper search plugin class
/​src/​Spryker/​Zed/​Search/​Dependency/​Plugin/​PageMapInterface.php buildPageMap

  • If there's no result formatter given then the raw search result will be returned

  • The formatted search result will be an associative array where the keys are the name and the values are the formatted results
getSearchConfig

  • Returns a statically cached instance (for performance reasons) of the search configuration

  • The result is the union of the hard-coded and the dynamic configurations

  • Dynamic configuration is provided by \Spryker\Client\Search\SearchDependencyProvider::createSearchConfigExpanderPlugins()
searchKeys

  • Runs a simple full text search for the given search string

  • Returns the raw result set ordered by relevance
searchQueryString

  • Runs a string search for the given search string

  • @see https://www.elastic.co/guide/en/elasticsearch/reference/2.4/query-dsl-query-string-query.html

  • Returns the raw result set ordered by relevance
read

  • Returns data from an external search service (e.g Elasticsearch)
write

  • Writes data into an external search service (e.g Elasticsearch)
delete

  • Deletes data from an external search service (e.g Elasticsearch)

 8.0.0

API (Facades)

Facade Method Description
install

  • Loads index definition json files from the folders

  • Installs Elasticsearch indexes and mapping types based on the loaded index definitions if they not exists already

  • For each configured store a separated index name is generated

  • The index is created for only the current store

  • The name of the index is automatically prefixed with the store name + underscore

  • Generates IndexMap class for each mapping type

  • The generated IndexMaps are not store specific and has the class name of the mapping types suffixed with "IndexMap"

  • The generated files will be removed and re-created always when install runs
getTotalCount

  • Returns the total number of documents in the current index
getMetaData

  • Returns the metadata information from the current index

  • Returns empty array if the index is not installed
delete

  • Removes the current index
getDocument

  • Returns a document from the current index with the given key in the given mapping type
searchKeys

  • Runs a simple full text search for the given search string

  • Returns the raw result set ordered by relevance
transformPageMapToDocument

{@inheritdoc}
transformPageMapToDocumentByMapperName

  • Transforms a raw data array into an Elasticsearch "page" mapping type document

  • The transformation is based on the given page map plugin name what configures which data goes into which field
generatePageIndexMap

  • Loads index definition json files from the folders

  • Generates IndexMap class for each mapping type

  • The generated IndexMaps are not store specific and has the class name of the mapping types suffixed with "IndexMap"

  • The generated files will be removed and re-created always when the command runs
createSnapshot

  • Creates a Snapshot.
existsSnapshot

  • Checks if a Snapshot exists.
deleteSnapshot

  • Deletes a Snapshot.
existsSnapshotRepository

  • Checks if a Snapshot repository exists.
createSnapshotRepository

  • Creates a Snapshot repository.
restoreSnapshot

  • Restores a Snapshot.
closeIndex

  • Closes an Index.
closeAllIndices

  • Closes all indices.
copyIndex

  • Copies one index to another index.

transformPageMapToDocument

  • Transforms a raw data array into an Elasticsearch "page" mapping type document

  • The transformation is based on the given page map what configures which data goes into which field
generatePageIndexMap

  • Loads index definition json files from the folders

  • Generates IndexMap class for each mapping type

  • The generated IndexMaps are not store specific and has the class name of the mapping types suffixed with "IndexMap"

  • The generated files will be removed and re-created always when the command runs

Clients

Client Method Description
checkConnection

  • Connects to Elasticsearch client if possible

  • Throws exception if connection fails
expandQuery

  • Expands the base search query with multiple query expanders

  • All expanders use the same search configuration provided by this client

  • The expanders use the given parameters to adapt to the request

  • Returns the expanded query
search

  • Runs the search query based on the search configuration provided by this client

  • If there's no result formatter given then the raw search result will be returned

  • The formatted search result will be an associative array where the keys are the name and the values are the formatted results
getSearchConfig

  • Returns a statically cached instance (for performance reasons) of the search configuration

  • The result is the union of the hard-coded and the dynamic configurations

  • Dynamic configuration is provided by \Spryker\Client\Search\SearchDependencyProvider::createSearchConfigExpanderPlugins()
searchKeys

  • Runs a simple full text search for the given search string

  • Returns the raw result set ordered by relevance

  • For each configured store a separated index will be created

  • The name of the index is automatically prefixed with the store name + underscore

  • Generates IndexMap class for each mapping type

  • The generated IndexMaps are not store specific and has the class name of the mapping types suffixed with "IndexMap"

  • The generated files will be removed and re-created always when install runs
getTotalCount

  • Returns the total number of documents in the current index
getMetaData

  • Returns the metadata information from the current index

  • Returns empty array if the index is not installed
delete

  • Removes the current index
getDocument

  • Returns a document from the current index with the given key in the given mapping type
searchKeys

  • Runs a simple full text search for the given search string

  • Returns the raw result set ordered by relevance
transformPageMapToDocument

  • Transforms a raw data array into an Elasticsearch "page" mapping type document

  • The transformation is based on the given page map what configures which data goes into which field

Clients

Client Method Description
checkConnection

  • Connects to Elasticsearch client if possible

  • Throws exception if connection fails
expandQuery

  • Expands the base search query with multiple query expanders

  • All expanders use the same search configuration provided by this client

  • The expanders use the given parameters to adapt to the request

  • Returns the expanded query
search

  • Runs the search query based on the search configuration provided by this client

  • If there's no result formatter given then the raw search result will be returned

  • The formatted search result will be an associative array where the keys are the name and the values are the formatted results
getSearchConfig

  • Returns a statically cached instance (for performance reasons) of the search configuration

  • The result is the union of the hard-coded and the dynamic configurations

  • Dynamic configuration is provided by \Spryker\Client\Search\SearchDependencyProvider::createSearchConfigExpanderPlugins()
searchKeys

  • Runs a simple full text search for the given search string

  • Returns the raw result set ordered by relevance
